[{"id":"VR627860","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VR627859.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">If the potential energy associated with <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F\"><math alttext=\"F\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>F</mi></math></span></span> is defined to be zero at infinite separation, what is the potential energy of the four-particle system while it is being held in the triangular pyramid arrangement shown?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR627860_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<html><body><div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram of 4 particles in the shape of a triangular pyramid. In the pyramid, each of the particles is a vertex, and the distance between each pair of particles is d.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR627859.g02.svg\"/></div><p class=\"passage_para\">Two particles of a certain type interact with each other with a repulsive conservative force with magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F equals the fraction alpha over r cubed, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"F equals the fraction alpha over r cubed, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>α</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mfrac></math></span></span> where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"alpha\"><math alttext=\"alpha\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi></math></span></span> is a constant and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r\"><math alttext=\"r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math></span></span> is the distance between the particles. A system of four such particles is held together to form a triangular pyramid with a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d\"><math alttext=\"d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math></span></span> between each pair of particles, as shown in the figure.</p></div></div></div></body></html>"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction 2 alpha, over d squared, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"the fraction 2 alpha, over d squared, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>α</mi></mrow><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction 3 alpha, over d squared, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"the fraction 3 alpha, over d squared, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>α</mi></mrow><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction 6 alpha, over d cubed, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"the fraction 6 alpha, over d cubed, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><mi>α</mi></mrow><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction negative 18 alpha, over d to the fourth power, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"the fraction negative 18 alpha, over d to the fourth power, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>18</mn><mi>α</mi></mrow><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>4</mn></msup></mfrac></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":1}]